sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Browser
    participant Django as Django (PasswordResetView)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant Email as Email Backend

    User->>Browser: Click "Forgot Password?" on login page
    Browser->>Django: GET /accounts/password-reset/
    Django-->>Browser: 200 password_reset.html (email form)

    User->>Browser: Enter email address
    Browser->>Django: POST /accounts/password-reset/
    Django->>DB: Look up User by email

    alt Email matches a known account
        Django->>Django: Generate uidb64 + signed token\n(valid 24 hours)
        Django->>Email: Send password_reset.txt\nwith reset link to user email
        Note over Email: In dev: prints to console\nIn prod: SMTP send
    else Email unknown
        Note over Django: No email sent\n(same response to prevent\nuser enumeration)
    end

    Django-->>Browser: 302 → /accounts/password-reset/done/
    Browser->>Django: GET /accounts/password-reset/done/
    Django-->>Browser: 200 password_reset_done.html\n("Check your email")

    User->>Browser: Click link in email
    Browser->>Django: GET /accounts/password-reset/confirm/<uidb64>/<token>/
    Django->>Django: Validate token signature and expiry

    alt Token valid
        Django-->>Browser: 302 → session-based URL\n(token consumed, stored in session)
        Browser->>Django: GET /accounts/password-reset/confirm/<uidb64>/set-password/
        Django-->>Browser: 200 password_reset_confirm.html (new password form)

        User->>Browser: Enter and confirm new password
        Browser->>Django: POST /accounts/password-reset/confirm/<uidb64>/set-password/
        Django->>Django: Validate passwords match\nand meet strength requirements

        alt Passwords valid
            Django->>DB: Set new password hash on User
            Django-->>Browser: 302 → /accounts/password-reset/complete/
            Browser->>Django: GET /accounts/password-reset/complete/
            Django-->>Browser: 200 password_reset_complete.html ("Password Updated")
        else Passwords invalid (mismatch or too weak)
            Django-->>Browser: 200 password_reset_confirm.html\n(form with errors)
        end

    else Token invalid or expired
        Django-->>Browser: 200 password_reset_confirm.html\n("Link Expired" state)
        Note over Browser: User directed to request a new link
    end
